---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Approach"
  description="Tutelare's perspective on AI code oversight: direct human attention to highest-risk AI-generated code; let adversarial AI handle the routine."
>
  <h1
    class="font-semibold leading-tight mb-6"
    style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem)"
  >
    Approach
  </h1>

  <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">
    <em>This page is a placeholder. Final Approach essay to follow.</em>
  </p>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      The principle
    </h2>
    <p>
      Direct human attention to the highest-risk AI-generated code. Let adversarial AI
      handle the routine. Sample what is cleared. Build the accountability structures
      that fit how humans and AI are now actually authoring code together.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      What this looks like in practice
    </h2>
    <p>[Placeholder. Risk-tiering of changes by impact, adversarial-AI review for non-flagged
      changes, statistical sampling of cleared code, accountability structures for human-AI
      authoring teams.]</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      What we are not claiming
    </h2>
    <p>[Placeholder. Honesty about uncertainty. The space is new. The patterns are emerging.
      We help organizations navigate this from a position of informed practice, not certainty.]</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
